comments:
Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Penzance, 
    Madron and Ludgvan.

Created 1.4.1934 by renaming the parish of St. Erth Urban. See 
    also Table 2, notes (b) and (c).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Madron in Penzance 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Penzance.

Unparished area created 1.4.1974 from the parish of Penzance. 
    Abolished 1.4.1980 to become the parish of Penzance.
Abolished 1.4.1974 to become the Penwith unparished area.

Created 1.4.1980 from the Penwith unparished area. See also 
    Table 2, note (c).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Penzance in Madron 
    Urban District. Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Penzance.

Abolished 1894 to become the separate parishes of St. Erth Urban 
    and St. Erth Rural.

Created 1.4.1934 by renaming the parish of St. Erth Rural. See 
    also Table 2, note (c).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of St. Erth. Renamed 
    1.4.1934 to become the parish of St. Erth.

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of St. Erth in Hayle 
    Urban District. Renamed 1.4.1934 to become the parish of Hayle.

Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of St. Ives 
    and Ludgvan.
